#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.102"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.102:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.102:0.2"
msgid "11. Valāhakavagga "
msgstr "11. Clouds "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.102:0.3"
msgid "102. Dutiyavalāhakasutta "
msgstr "102. Clouds (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.103, sc1
msgctxt "an4.102:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, valāhakā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of clouds. "

msgctxt "an4.102:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><ol>
msgctxt "an4.102:1.3"
msgid "Gajjitā no vassitā, vassitā no gajjitā, neva gajjitā no vassitā gajjitā ca vassitā ca. "
msgstr "~One thunders but doesn’t rain, ~one rains but doesn’t thunder, ~one neither thunders nor rains, and ~one both rains and thunders. "

#. HTML: </ol><p>
msgctxt "an4.102:1.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro valāhakā. "
msgstr "These are the four kinds of clouds. "

msgctxt "an4.102:1.5"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, cattāro valāhakūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "In the same way, these four people similar to clouds are found in the world. "

msgctxt "an4.102:1.6"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><ol>
msgctxt "an4.102:1.7"
msgid "Gajjitā no vassitā, vassitā no gajjitā, neva gajjitā no vassitā, gajjitā ca vassitā ca. "
msgstr "~One thunders but doesn’t rain, ~one rains but doesn’t thunder, ~one neither thunders nor rains, and ~one both rains and thunders. "

#. HTML: </ol><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.102:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo gajjitā hoti, no vassitā? "
msgstr "And how does a person thunder but not rain? "

msgctxt "an4.102:2.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇāti—"
msgstr "It’s when a person memorizes the teaching—"

msgctxt "an4.102:2.3"
msgid "suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ. "
msgstr "statements, songs, discussions, verses, inspired exclamations, legends, stories of past lives, amazing stories, and classifications. "

msgctxt "an4.102:2.4"
msgid "So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti. "
msgstr "But they don’t truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’. "

msgctxt "an4.102:2.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo gajjitā hoti, no vassitā. "
msgstr "That’s how a person thunders but doesn’t rain. "

msgctxt "an4.102:2.6"
msgid "Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, valāhako gajjitā, no vassitā; "
msgstr "That person is like a cloud that thunders but doesn’t rain, I say. "

msgctxt "an4.102:2.7"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.102:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo vassitā hoti, no gajjitā? "
msgstr "And how does a person rain but not thunder? "

msgctxt "an4.102:3.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo dhammaṃ na pariyāpuṇāti—"
msgstr "It’s when a person doesn’t memorize the teaching … "

msgctxt "an4.102:3.3"
msgid "suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.102:3.4"
msgid "So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti. "
msgstr "But they truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … "

msgctxt "an4.102:3.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo vassitā hoti, no gajjitā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.102:3.6"
msgid "Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, valāhako vassitā, no gajjitā; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.102:3.7"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an4.102:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo neva gajjitā hoti, no vassitā? "
msgstr "And how does a person neither thunder nor rain? "

msgctxt "an4.102:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo neva dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇāti—"
msgstr "It’s when a person doesn’t memorize the teaching … "

msgctxt "an4.102:4.3"
msgid "suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.102:4.4"
msgid "So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti. "
msgstr "Nor do they truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … "

msgctxt "an4.102:4.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo neva gajjitā hoti, no vassitā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.102:4.6"
msgid "Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, valāhako neva gajjitā, no vassitā; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.102:4.7"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.104, sc5
msgctxt "an4.102:5.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, puggalo gajjitā ca hoti vassitā ca? "
msgstr "And how does a person both thunder and rain? "

msgctxt "an4.102:5.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇāti—"
msgstr "It’s when a person memorizes the teaching … "

msgctxt "an4.102:5.3"
msgid "suttaṃ, geyyaṃ, veyyākaraṇaṃ, gāthaṃ, udānaṃ, itivuttakaṃ, jātakaṃ, abbhutadhammaṃ, vedallaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.102:5.4"
msgid "So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti. "
msgstr "And they truly understand: ‘This is suffering’ … "

msgctxt "an4.102:5.5"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puggalo gajjitā ca hoti vassitā ca. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.102:5.6"
msgid "Seyyathāpi so, bhikkhave, valāhako gajjitā ca vassitā ca; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.102:5.7"
msgid "tathūpamāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imaṃ puggalaṃ vadāmi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.102:5.8"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro valāhakūpamā puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti. "
msgstr "These four people similar to clouds are found in the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.102:5.9"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

